    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-IR-Sensor">
      <title>IR Sensor </title>
      <p>
        IR sensor is an electronic sensor which measures and detects any object around the surroundings. There are two kind of IR sensor, active and passive, active infrared sensor has two parts LED and a receiver. When the object is closer the infra-red light emitted from the LED will hit the object and reflect back to the receiver.
      </p>
      <figure>
        <image source="/images/ir_sensor.jpg" width="40%"/>
        <caption>components required for the experiment</caption>
      </figure>
      <term>IR sensor VS Proximity </term>
      <p>
        Active sensor is also called as proximity sensor, (ultrasonic sensor). Active sensor will be used for calculating distance. Passive infrared sensor will only detect the IR radiation from the object. IR sensor acts in a same way of how PIR sensor acts.
      </p>
      <p>
        IR sensor has two LED one acts as emitter and other one acts as a transmitter. When the sensor detects an object, the emitter will send an infra light to the object and the object will reflect back the rays to the receiver. When the receiver receives the IR signal, it will trigger the micro controller to execute accordingly. It has three pins VCC, GND, D0. Each pin of IR sensor is explained in detail. In table 3.3.3, the pin configuration about the sensor is described with its purpose.
      </p>
