<subsection xml:id="subsec-Code-sanitizer">
  <title>Code</title>
  <program>
    #include &lt;Servo.h &gt;//library for servo motor
      Servo motor;
      int IRSensor=8;//declare IRsensor 
      void setup()
      {
      Serial.begin(9600);//initialize Serial communication
      motor.attach(9);//declare servo motor
      pinMode(IRSensor, INPUT);//mode declaration for IR sensor
      }
      void loop ()
      {
      int statusSensor=digitalRead(IRSensor);
      if(statusSensor==1)// detects the presence of IR
      {
      motor.write(0);
      delay (1000);
      motor.write(180);//rotate 180 degree
      delay (100);//delay in micro seconds
      }      
      delay (1000);
      }      
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation </term>
 <ol> 
  <li>
    <p>
      As we are familiar with the smart dustbin, we should install the library for servo motor.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Declaring pins of IR sensor and servo motor for 8th  and 9th  pins to Arduino respectively. 
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Declaring servo motor function as Servo motor (). 
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      In void setup function initialize motor using motor. Attach (9).
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Initialize the IR sensor as input using PinMode function 
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      In void loop function the value of IRSensor will be stored as digital data using digital Read() function.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      When the sensor finds the object, the value will be set to high, when the value is high the motor will rotate for 180 degrees with the delay of 1 second.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      When motor rotates 180-degree rotation will pull the knob of the sanitizer to dispense the sanitizer.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
